1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:05,145
When you start the activities, they will follow the same order as this lesson.

2
00:00:05,095 --> 00:00:14,741
First, you do a warm-up: Check the device is charged, the keyboard and mouse are connected, and you can sit comfortably with the screen at a good distance.

3
00:00:14,741 --> 00:00:19,293
Then you answer quick checks, so we know the key words make sense.

4
00:00:19,293 --> 00:00:25,489
Next, you practise the real computer skill: Complete the full start-up routine twice.

5
00:00:25,489 --> 00:00:30,067
First time with staff prompts, second time with fewer prompts.

6
00:00:30,067 --> 00:00:36,059
You may also type a short answer, for example: Type a practice password to sign in.

7
00:00:36,059 --> 00:00:44,429
At the end, you finish with a stretch or reflection: Open the Start menu, find the power option, and identify Shut down.

8
00:00:44,429 --> 00:00:47,812
Staff can complete the final click if needed.

9
00:00:47,812 --> 00:00:50,363
Take one activity at a time.

10
00:00:50,363 --> 00:00:54,904
If you need help, ask staff, then try the next step yourself.

